# Afenda Coding Session (always on)

Full skill: `.cursor/skills/afenda-coding-session/SKILL.md` — invoke with `/afenda-coding-session` for implementation detail.

**Announce at start of every coding turn:** "I'm using afenda-coding-session — stating the execution contract before edits."

## Phase 0 — before any Write/StrReplace (mandatory)

State all six lines. Do **not** edit code until done:

1. **Objective** — one sentence
2. **Allowed layer** — single package/path (see skill §2)
3. **Files to change** — explicit list
4. **Prohibited** — packages/paths off limits
5. **Authority** — Architecture · Design System · UI Governance · Metadata · Kernel · Database · Permission
6. **Acceptance gates** — which `pnpm` commands will run

Before claiming "no pending decision" or "no migration planned", search **`docs/adr/`** and **`docs/PAS/`** — not PRs alone.

If upstream contract is missing: **stop and report**. No local registries, tokens, permissions, or tenant resolvers.

**PAS:** For foundation/package work, read [`foundation-delivery-authority.md`](../../docs/architecture/foundation-delivery-authority.md) and derive Phase 0 from registry + `docs/PAS/slice/` handoffs.

## Phase 1 — implement

Follow skill §3–§10. Hard stops (skill §0.1): consumer defining owned contracts, unauthorized cross-package imports, hand-edited migrations, mocking governance instead of canonical resolvers.

## Phase 2 — before ending turn (mandatory)

Post the **Completion Report** (skill §11): objective, files changed, authority followed, drift-prevention pass/fail table, gates run, known gaps.

Any drift row **Fail** → fix or escalate. Code without evidence is not done.
